col[][] Matrix
----------------------
| i\j | 0 | 1 | 2 | 3 |
|-----|---|---|---|---|
|  0  | 1 | 1 | 1 | 0 |
|  1  | 2 | 0 | 2 | 1 |
|  2  | 3 | 1 | 3 | 0 |
|  3  | 4 | 0 | 4 | 1 |
----------------------

âœ… Dry Run from Bottom Right:
We go from bottom-right cell to top-left.

ğŸŸ¨ Cell (3,3)
row[3][3] = 2, col[3][3] = 1 â†’ s = min(2, 1) = 1

Check:

row[3][3] = 2 âœ…

col[3][3] = 1 âœ…

row[3 - s + 1][3] = row[3][3] = 2 â‰¥ 1 âœ…

col[3][3 - s + 1] = col[3][3] = 1 â‰¥ 1 âœ…

âœ… res = 1

ğŸŸ¨ Cell (3,2)
row[3][2] = 1, col[3][2] = 4 â†’ s = 1

All conditions valid â†’ âœ… res = 1 (no change)

ğŸŸ¨ Cell (3,1)
row[3][1] = 0 â†’ s = 0 â†’ âŒ Skip

ğŸŸ¨ Cell (3,0)
row[3][0] = 1, col[3][0] = 4 â†’ s = 1

âœ… All good â†’ res = 1 (still)

ğŸŸ¨ Cell (2,2)
row[2][2] = 3, col[2][2] = 3 â†’ s = 3

Check top-left:

row[2 - 3 + 1][2] = row[0][2] = 3 âœ…

col[2][2 - 3 + 1] = col[2][0] = 3 âœ…

âœ… res = 3 ğŸ‰

Remaining cells:
Other cells will have s <= 3, but will not satisfy both border conditions for s = 3 or are smaller than 3 already. So, res stays at 3.

âœ… Final Answer: res = 3
